OL,3,CPolice officers used reasonable force
OL,4,Cto restrain 23-year-old who later died
OL,6,F"When someone dies either during or
OL,7,Ffollowing detention, it is important
OL,8,Fthat the circumstances are thoroughly
OL,9,Fand independently investigated.
OL,11,F"From the evidence we gathered we were
OL,12,Fsatisfied that the force used by
OL,13,Fofficers in trying to arrest and
OL,14,Frestrain Mr Allford, was necessary,
OL,15,Freasonable and proportionate in the
OL,16,Fcircumstances, as was the force used
OL,17,Fto try to prevent him from ingesting
OL,18,Fwhat were believed to be class A
OL,19,Fdrugs."
